EN: Project Overview
Summary
EUGENE OS is a custom 64-bit operating system built from scratch for the x86-64 architecture. It features a monolithic assembly-based kernel and a C-based graphical user interface (GUI). The system implements multitasking, a FAT32 file system driver, and a window management engine.

Key Features
1. UEFI Bootloader
Implemented as a native UEFI PE64 application.

Initializes high-resolution video modes using the Graphics Output Protocol (GOP).

Detects hardware specifications (CPU Brand, RAM size, Disk capacity) via UEFI Boot Services.

Locates and loads the kernel binary (kernel.bin) from a FAT32 partition into memory at 0x100000.

2. Kernel Architecture
Language: Pure x86-64 Assembly (FASM).

Interrupt Handling: Configured IDT (Interrupt Descriptor Table) for handling CPU exceptions (0-31) and system calls via int 0x80.

Multitasking: Preemptive task scheduler driven by the PIT timer. Supports background tasks and userland application execution.

Memory Management: Kernel-level heap manager providing kmalloc and kfree functionality.

Hardware Drivers:

Storage: ATA PIO mode for sector-level disk I/O.

FileSystem: Robust FAT32 driver supporting file/directory creation, deletion, reading, and traversal.

Input: PS/2 Keyboard driver with FIFO buffering; PS/2 Mouse driver with packet parsing and coordinate tracking.

Audio: PC Speaker frequency generation using PIT.

3. Userland & GUI Environment
Custom LibC: Independent implementation of essential C functions (memory allocation, string manipulation, sprintf, POSIX-style I/O wrappers).

Window Manager: * Double-buffered rendering to prevent screen flickering.

Z-order management (active window focus).

Event-driven mouse interaction: Window dragging, minimizing, and closing.

Built-in Applications:

C-Shell Console: Terminal emulator with command history and system utilities.

Text Editor: Feature-rich editor with cursor support, arrow-key navigation, and file saving.

File Explorer: Graphical VFS browser with file execution capabilities.

Technical Specifications
Codebase: ~90% Assembly (FASM), ~10% C (GCC/MinGW).

Executable Format: Flat binary for the kernel and applications.

Memory Map:

0x1000000: Video/File Buffer.

0x2000000: VFS Directory Buffer.

0x4000000: Userland Application Base.

0x8000000: Userland Heap.

Build Instructions
The project uses a custom build.bat script that requires:

FASM (for bootloader and kernel).

MinGW-w64 GCC/LD (for C userland).

QEMU (for emulation with OVMF BIOS).
